qas.question: What appointment did Eisenhower receive in November of 1942?

answers.text: Supreme Commander Allied Expeditionary Force of the North African Theater of Operations

qas.question: What was the code name of the North African campaign?
At what location was the North African campaign planned?
How many years before Eisenhower's command had a non-Briton commanded Gibraltar?

context: In November 1942, he was also appointed <a0_0>Supreme Commander Allied Expeditionary Force of the North African Theater of Operations<a0_0/> (NATOUSA) through the new operational Headquarters Allied (Expeditionary) Force Headquarters (A(E)FHQ). The word "expeditionary" was dropped soon after his appointment for security reasons. The campaign in North Africa was designated <a1_0>Operation Torch<a1_0/> and was planned underground within the <a2_0>Rock of Gibraltar<a2_0/>. Eisenhower was the first non-British person to command Gibraltar in <a3_0>200<a3_0/> years.
